reviews.review_text: Sentimental favorite It's hard for me to be impartial about this show. I took my wife and step-daughter to this one, sat in the top row of the balcony, but the sound was fine. Ran into Menke before the acoustic set, already in the zone. Told me they did Ripple the previous night. Odis wandering around at the end of the set was so mellow. After 'Stranger/Sugaree, the kid turns to me and says," Now I know why you like The Grateful Dead so much". You don't get that sort of validation very often. Appreciative to have an AUD, but would love a SBD someday. A must have for me, but judge for yourself. 3 plus stars, call it a 4. Decent Aud.(Thanks Bob)
